store |accessdate=2014-05-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427231924/http://www.licollectiblesstore.com/product/americas-funniest-home-videos-mirco-movie-viewer |archivedate=April 27, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[America's Funniest People]]'', people intentionally being humorous, also produced by Vin Di Bona\n* ''[[Australia's Funniest Home Video Show]]'', 1990\u20132004 show created by Di Bona\n* ''[[Australia's Funniest Home Videos]]'', post-2005 show created by Di Bona\n* ''[[Australia's Naughtiest Home Videos]]'', a similar show created by Di Bona\n* ''[[It Only Hurts When I Laugh (TV Series)|It Only Hurts When I Laugh]]'', a [[truTV]] series\n* ''[[New Zealand's Funniest Home Videos]]'' (later ''The Kiwi Video Show'')\n* ''[[Ridiculousness (TV series)|Ridiculousness]]'', an [[MTV]] series using internet videos\n* ''[[The Planet's Funniest Animals]]'', an [[Animal Planet]] series\n* ''[[The World's Funniest Moments]]'', a syndicated series\n* ''[[The World's Funniest!]]'', a 1997\u20132000 series on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX]]\n* ''[[Video Gag]]'', the French equivalent of ''AFHV''\n* ''[[You've Been Framed]]'', the British equivalent of the show\n* ''[[\u015amiechu warte]]'', in [[Poland|Polish]] programs in [[TVP1]] production [[TVP3 Szczecin]] in [[Szczecin]] (Polish equivalent of the show)\n* ''[[Juoko \u012fvykiai]]'' in [[Lithuania]] equivalent of the show\n* ''[[Video loco (Chilean TV show)|Video Loco]]'', Chilean equivalent of the show\n* ''[[F\u00f3rky a Vtipky]] programs in [[Slovakia]] on [[Plus (TV channel, Slovakia)|Plus]]\n* ''[[Upps! \u2013 Die Pannenshow]]'', in [[Germany|German]] programs in [[Super RTL]] \n* ''[[Nejz\u00e1bavn\u011bj\u0161\u00ed dom\u00e1c\u00ed videa Ameriky]]'' In [[Czech Republic]] programs\n* ''[[L\u00e5t Kameran G\u00e5]]'', [[Sweden|Swedish]] equivalent of the show\n* ''[[De Leukste Thuis]]'', [[Netherlands|Dutch]] equivalent of the show\n* ''[[Videos de primera]]'', [[Spain|Spanish]] equivalent of the show\n* ''Paperissima'', [[Italy|Italian]] equivalent of the show\n* ''Dr\u00f4le de vid\u00e9o'', [[French-Canadian]] equivalent of the show airing on [[T\u00e9l\u00e9toon la Nuit]]\n* ''Isto S\u00f3 Video'', [[Portugal]]ian equivalent of the show\n* ''\u0421\u0430\u043c \u0421\u0435\u0431\u0435 \u0420\u0435\u0436\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0451\u0440'', [[Russia]]n equivalent of the show\n* ''Det' Ren Kagemand'', [[Denmark|Danish]] equivalent of the show\n* ''Ay, caramba!'', [[Mexico|Mexican]] equivalent of the show\n* ''Cs\u00ed\u00ed\u00edz!'', [[Hungary|Magyar]] equivalent of the show\n* ''S\u00fcper Matrak'', [[Turkey|Turkish]] equivalent of the show aired on [[Disney Channel]] Turkey\n*  ''Tak nev\u00e1hej a to\u010d!'' and ''Nato\u010dto!'',  [[Czech Republic|Czech]] equivalents of the show\n* \n<!--\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:13em;\"| Country / Region\n! style=\"width:15em;\"| Network(s)\n! style=\"width:15em;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:13em;\"| Aired as\n|-\n| {{GER}}\n| [[Super RTL]]\n| 2005 - present\n| ''[[Upps! Upps! \u2013 Die Pannenshow]]\n|-\n| {{UK}}\n| [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]\n| 1990 - present.\n| ''[[You've Been Framed]]''\n|-\n| {{POL}}\n| [[TVP1]]\n| 1994 - 2009\n| ''[[\u015amiechu \u015amiechu Warte]]''\n|-\n| {{ESP}}\n| [[TVE1]]\n| 1990 - 1998\n| ''[[Videos Videos de Primera]]''\n|-\n| {{SWE}}\n| [[TV3 (Sweden)|TV3]]\n| 1991 - 1997\n| ''[[L\u00e5t L\u00e5t kameran g\u00e5]]''\n|-\n| {{GBR}}\n| [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]\n| 1990 - present\n| ''[[You've Been Framed!]]\n|-\n| {{AUS}}\n| [[Nine Network]]\n| 1990 - 2014\n| ''[[Australia's Funniest Home Videos]]''\n|-\n| {{FRA}}\n| [[TF1]]\n| 1990 - 2008\n| ''[[Video Gag]]''\n|-\n| {{NLD}}\n| [[TROS]]\n| 1990 - 2004\n| ''[[De De Leukste Thuis]]''\n|-\n| {{BEL}}\n| [[VTM (TV channel)|VTM]]\n| 1990 - 2004\n| ''[[Videodinges Videodinges]]''\n|-\n| {{NLD}}\n| [[SBS 6]]\n| 2002 - present\n| ''[[Lachen Lachen om Home Video's]]''\n|-\n|}-->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.afv.com}}\n* {{IMDb title|id=0098740|title=America's Funniest Home Videos}}\n* {{tv.com show|americas-funniest-home-videos|America's Funniest Home Videos}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070603065822/http://www.shoutfactory.com/browse/5/americas_funniest_home_videos.aspx America's Funniest Home Videos] page from [[Shout! Factory]]\n\n{{ABCNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n\n[[Category:1989 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1980s American comedy television series]]\n[[Category:1990s American video clip television series]]\n[[Category:2000s American video clip television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American video clip television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American video clip television series]]\n[[Category:American Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by Disney\u2013ABC Domestic Television]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:American television series based on Japanese television series]]\n", "name_user": "JeffreyLoeber", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e1989\u20131997: Bob Saget", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/America%27s_Funniest_Home_Videos"}
{"title_page": "2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=2020 coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|timestamp=20200402133413|year=2020|month=April|day=2|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=2020 hotspot in Delhi|date=2 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox event\n| title                    = <!-- Title to display, if other than page name -->\n| image                    =\n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  =\n| native_name              = \n| native_name_lang         = \n| english_name             = \n| time                     =\n| duration                 = \n| date                     = 1 March - 21 March (Congregation) \n| venue                    = [[Banglewali Mosque]] \n| location                 = [[Delhi]], [[India]]\n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            = COVID-19 Hotspot \n| type                     = Religious congregation \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = \n| motive                   =\n| target                   = \n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organisers               = <!-- or |organizers= -->\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             = \n| awards                   = \n| url                      = \n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| notes                    = \n}}\n\nA [[Tablighi Jamaat]] religious congregation event that took place in Delhi's [[Banglewali Mosque]]  in early March has emerged as a  virus hotspot after numerous cases across India were traced back to the event. The congregation held in early March until the declaration of a [[2020 coronavirus lockdown in India|nationwide lockdown]], was attended by people from across India as well as other countries. About 200 people have shown symptoms of Flu of which, 24 people have been confirmed positive in Delhi.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-52104753|title=India event sparks massive search for Covid-19 cases|date=2020-03-31|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-31|language=en-GB}}</ref> Over 300 cases, including six deaths across the country were found to be linked to the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/opinion/tablighi-jamaat-congregation-and-how-religion-has-been-the-super-spreader-of-coronavirus/392531/|title=Tablighi Jamaat congregation and how religion has been the 'super spreader' of coronavirus|last=Team|first=ThePrint|date=2020-04-01|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gulte.com/news/83733/More-Than-330-Cases-Linked-to-Delhi-Mosque|title=More Than 330 Cases Linked to Delhi Mosque|last=13|date=2020-04-02|website=Gulte|language=english|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> The state of [[Tamil Nadu]] reported more than 190 cases linked to the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-india-delhi-markaz-nizamuddin-mosque-sealed-after-7-covid-19-deaths-850-moved-out-for-qu-2203336|title=50 Coronavirus Cases In Tamil Nadu After Delhi Mosque Event: 10 Points|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nQuestions have been raised as to how the [[Delhi Police]] and the [[Government of India]] allowed this event to proceed in the midst of a pandemic,<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tablighi-jamaat-markaz-timeline-delhi-police-mha-1662197-2020-04-01 Timeline of how Delhi Police, government made Markaz a ticking time bomb], India Today, 1 April 2020.</ref> while a similar event was prohibited in Mumbai by the [[Maharashtra Police]].<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/when-maharashtra-police-cancelled-a-parallel-bigger-tablighi-jamaat-event-to-avoid-covid-19-spread-1662540-2020-04-02 When Maharashtra Police cancelled a parallel, bigger Tablighi Jamaat event to avoid Covid-19 spread], India Today, 2 April 2020.</ref>\n\n==Attendees==\n\nThe event saw over 2000 attendees from all over the country and saw over 800 Indonesian and Malaysian preachers present. Many of these attendees are untraceable and are absconding.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/india/1828919/delhis-tablighi-jamaat-event-becomes-indias-coronavirus-hotspot/|title=A religious congregation in Delhi could be the coronavirus hotspot India was trying to escape|first=Niharika|last=Sharma|website=Quartz India}}</ref> 281 foreigners among 1830 people who had been staying at the mosque since 8 March were found by Delhi Police.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Aftermath==\nThere was Ijtema (congregation) in every week of March till March 21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/2100-foreigners-visited-india-for-tablighi-activities-this-year-mha/articleshow/74915572.cms|title=2100 foreigners visited India for Tablighi activities this year: MHA|date=March 31, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/nizamuddin-corona-cases-govts-race-to-curb-spread-as-hundreds-from-tablighi-meet-show-coronavirus-symptoms/articleshow/74921860.cms|title=Nizamuddin corona cases: Govts race to curb spread as hundreds from Tablighi meet show symptoms &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> There were also other violation of rules by foreign speakers including misuse of tourist visa for missionary activities and not taking 14-day home quarantine for travellers from abroad.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Singh|first=Vijaita|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/home-ministry-to-blacklist-800-tablighi-preachers-from-indonesia-for-violation-of-visa-rules/article31214048.ece|title=Home Ministry asked States to identify 824 foreign Tablighi members|date=2020-03-31|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> It is believed that the sources of infection were preachers from Indonesia. At least 24 of the attendees had tested positive for the virus among 300 who showed symptom by 31 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-52104753 |title=Coronavirus: Search for hundreds of people after Delhi prayer meeting |date=31 March 2020 |work=BBC }}</ref> Many had returned to their states and also provided refuge to foreign speakers without the knowledge of local governments.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Saravanan|first=S. p|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/covid-19-five-tourists-from-thailand-admitted-to-isolation-ward-at-erode-hospital/article31088949.ece|title=COVID-19 {{!}} Five tourists from Thailand admitted to isolation ward at Erode hospital|date=2020-03-17|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> and eventually started local transmissions especially in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[Telengana]], [[Karnataka]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]] and [[Assam]]. On 16 March 2020, Delhi Government ordered that no religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 will be allowed in Delhi till 31 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/covid-19-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-protests-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-mar-31/articleshow/74650645.cms|title=Coronavirus in Delhi: No religious, social, political gatherings, protests of over 50 in Delhi till Mar 31 &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-outbreak-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-march-31/articleshow/74650421.cms?from=mdr|title=Coronavirus outbreak: No religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 in Delhi till March 31|date=March 16, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> As of 30 March 2020 the entire [[Nizamuddin West]] area has been cordoned off by the Police and medical camps have been set up.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/coronavirus-200-people-from-nizamuddin-develop-symptoms-area-cordoned-off/article31204617.ece|title=Coronavirus &#124; 200 people in Nizamuddin develop symptoms; area cordoned off|first=Saurabh|last=Trivedi|date=March 30, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref> After evacuation from the markaz, of the scores of jamaat attendees, 167 of them were quarantined in a railway facility in south east Delhi amid concerns over their safety and transmission of the virus. There were further complications after the staff at the quarantine facility reported the Tablighi jamaat followers misbehaved with the staff and spit at the doctors looking after them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-india-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-misbehave-staffers-spit-doctors-delhi-quarantine-units-1662322-2020-04-01|title=Tablighi Jamaat attendees misbehave with staffers, spit at doctors at Delhi quarantine units|last=DelhiApril 1|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=April 1|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02|last3=Ist|first3=2020 22:59}}</ref>\n\nAdministration of TJ had said they are willing to dispatch hundreds of missionary to their respective nation & states but as the lockdown is in place they are helpless.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/nizamuddin-markaz-had-sought-help-from-authorities-for-vacating-premises/article31214305.ece|title=Nizamuddin markaz had sought help from authorities for vacating premises|first=Staff|last=Reporter|date=March 31, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>Press Release and relevant letters released by the Markaz</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://khabar.ndtv.com/news/india/coronavirus-total-case-in-india-nizamuddin-markaz-organiser-says-continuously-asking-curfew-pass-and-2203440|title=\u0915\u094c\u0928 \u0939\u0948 '\u0918\u094b\u0930 \u0905\u092a\u0930\u093e\u0927\u0940': \u0905\u0917\u0930 \u0924\u092c\u0932\u0940\u0917\u0940 \u091c\u092e\u093e\u0924 \u0928\u0947 \u092e\u093e\u0902\u0917\u093e \u0925\u093e 17 \u0917\u093e\u0921\u093c\u093f\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092b\u094d\u092f\u0942 \u092a\u093e\u0938, \u0924\u094b \u0915\u093f\u0938\u0928\u0947 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u0938\u0941\u0928\u0940 \u092c\u093e\u0924|website=NDTVIndia}}</ref>\n\n==Death toll==\n\nTotal Deaths of participants (as of 1 April) : 19\n\n* [[Telangana]]: 9\n* [[Delhi]]: 2\n* [[Jammu and Kashmir]]: 2\n* [[Maharashtra]]: 2\n* [[Andhra Pradesh]]: 1\n* [[Gujarat]]: 1\n* [[Karnataka]]: 1\n* [[Bihar]]: 1\n\n==Action==\n\nDelhi government ordered an FIR against [[Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi]], the head of Nizamuddin faction of the Tablighi Jamat.<ref name=\"standard\">{{cite web |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-120033100007_1.html |website=business-standard |publisher=[[Business Standard]] |accessdate=30 March 2020 |date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatoday\">{{cite web |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-1661514-2020-03-30 |website=India Today |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref> On 31 March 2020, FIR was filed against [[Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi]] and others by Delhi Police Crime Branch under Section 3 (penalty for offence) of the [[Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897]] and Sections 269 (Negligent act likely to spread infection of disease), 270 (malignant act likely to spread infection of disease), 271 (disobedience to quarantine rule) and 120b (punishment of criminal conspiracy) of the IPC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-in-india-tablighi-jamaat-preacher-others-booked-for-violating-govt-guidelines-on-religious-gatherings-1661870-2020-03-31|title=Coronavirus in India: Tablighi Jamaat preacher, others booked for violating govt guidelines on religious gatherings|first1=India Today Web Desk New|last1=DelhiMarch 31|first2=2020UPDATED:|last2=March 31|first3=2020 21:56|last3=Ist|website=India Today}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in India]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=2020 coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|timestamp=20200402133413|year=2020|month=April|day=2|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=2020 hotspot in Delhi|date=2 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox event\n| title                    = <!-- Title to display, if other than page name -->\n| image                    =\n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  =\n| native_name              = \n| native_name_lang         = \n| english_name             = \n| time                     =\n| duration                 = \n| date                     = 1 March - 21 March (Congregation) \n| venue                    = [[Banglewali Mosque]] \n| location                 = [[[Delhi]], India\n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            = COVID-19 Hotspot \n| type                     = Religious congregation \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = \n| motive                   =\n| target                   = \n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organisers               = <!-- or |organizers= -->\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             = \n| awards                   = \n| url                      = \n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| notes                    = \n}}\n\nA [[Tablighi Jamaat]] religious congregation event that took place in Delhi's [[Banglewali Mosque]]  in early March has emerged as a  virus hotspot after numerous cases across India were traced back to the event. The congregation held in early March until the declaration of a [[2020 coronavirus lockdown in India|nationwide lockdown]], was attended by people from across India as well as other countries. About 200 people have shown symptoms of Flu of which, 24 people have been confirmed positive in Delhi.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-52104753|title=India event sparks massive search for Covid-19 cases|date=2020-03-31|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-31|language=en-GB}}</ref> Over 300 cases, including six deaths across the country were found to be linked to the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/opinion/tablighi-jamaat-congregation-and-how-religion-has-been-the-super-spreader-of-coronavirus/392531/|title=Tablighi Jamaat congregation and how religion has been the 'super spreader' of coronavirus|last=Team|first=ThePrint|date=2020-04-01|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gulte.com/news/83733/More-Than-330-Cases-Linked-to-Delhi-Mosque|title=More Than 330 Cases Linked to Delhi Mosque|last=13|date=2020-04-02|website=Gulte|language=english|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> The state of [[Tamil Nadu]] reported more than 190 cases linked to the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-india-delhi-markaz-nizamuddin-mosque-sealed-after-7-covid-19-deaths-850-moved-out-for-qu-2203336|title=50 Coronavirus Cases In Tamil Nadu After Delhi Mosque Event: 10 Points|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nQuestions have been raised as to how the [[Delhi Police]] and the [[Government of India]] allowed this event to proceed in the midst of a pandemic,<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tablighi-jamaat-markaz-timeline-delhi-police-mha-1662197-2020-04-01 Timeline of how Delhi Police, government made Markaz a ticking time bomb], India Today, 1 April 2020.</ref> while a similar event was prohibited in Mumbai by the [[Maharashtra Police]].<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/when-maharashtra-police-cancelled-a-parallel-bigger-tablighi-jamaat-event-to-avoid-covid-19-spread-1662540-2020-04-02 When Maharashtra Police cancelled a parallel, bigger Tablighi Jamaat event to avoid Covid-19 spread], India Today, 2 April 2020.</ref>\n\n==Attendees==\n\nThe event saw over 2000 attendees from all over the country and saw over 800 Indonesian and Malaysian preachers present. Many of these attendees are untraceable and are absconding.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/india/1828919/delhis-tablighi-jamaat-event-becomes-indias-coronavirus-hotspot/|title=A religious congregation in Delhi could be the coronavirus hotspot India was trying to escape|first=Niharika|last=Sharma|website=Quartz India}}</ref> 281 foreigners among 1830 people who had been staying at the mosque since 8 March were found by Delhi Police.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Aftermath==\nThere was Ijtema (congregation) in every week of March till March 21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/2100-foreigners-visited-india-for-tablighi-activities-this-year-mha/articleshow/74915572.cms|title=2100 foreigners visited India for Tablighi activities this year: MHA|date=March 31, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/nizamuddin-corona-cases-govts-race-to-curb-spread-as-hundreds-from-tablighi-meet-show-coronavirus-symptoms/articleshow/74921860.cms|title=Nizamuddin corona cases: Govts race to curb spread as hundreds from Tablighi meet show symptoms &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> There were also other violation of rules by foreign speakers including misuse of tourist visa for missionary activities and not taking 14-day home quarantine for travellers from abroad.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Singh|first=Vijaita|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/home-ministry-to-blacklist-800-tablighi-preachers-from-indonesia-for-violation-of-visa-rules/article31214048.ece|title=Home Ministry asked States to identify 824 foreign Tablighi members|date=2020-03-31|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> It is believed that the sources of infection were preachers from Indonesia. At least 24 of the attendees had tested positive for the virus among 300 who showed symptom by 31 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-52104753 |title=Coronavirus: Search for hundreds of people after Delhi prayer meeting |date=31 March 2020 |work=BBC }}</ref> Many had returned to their states and also provided refuge to foreign speakers without the knowledge of local governments.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Saravanan|first=S. p|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/covid-19-five-tourists-from-thailand-admitted-to-isolation-ward-at-erode-hospital/article31088949.ece|title=COVID-19 {{!}} Five tourists from Thailand admitted to isolation ward at Erode hospital|date=2020-03-17|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> and eventually started local transmissions especially in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[Telengana]], [[Karnataka]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]] and [[Assam]]. On 16 March 2020, Delhi Government ordered that no religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 will be allowed in Delhi till 31 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/covid-19-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-protests-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-mar-31/articleshow/74650645.cms|title=Coronavirus in Delhi: No religious, social, political gatherings, protests of over 50 in Delhi till Mar 31 &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-outbreak-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-march-31/articleshow/74650421.cms?from=mdr|title=Coronavirus outbreak: No religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 in Delhi till March 31|date=March 16, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> As of 30 March 2020 the entire [[Nizamuddin West]] area has been cordoned off by the Police and medical camps have been set up.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/coronavirus-200-people-from-nizamuddin-develop-symptoms-area-cordoned-off/article31204617.ece|title=Coronavirus &#124; 200 people in Nizamuddin develop symptoms; area cordoned off|first=Saurabh|last=Trivedi|date=March 30, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref> After evacuation from the markaz, of the scores of jamaat attendees, 167 of them were quarantined in a railway facility in south east Delhi amid concerns over their safety and transmission of the virus. There were further complications after the staff at the quarantine facility reported the Tablighi jamaat followers misbehaved with the staff and spit at the doctors looking after them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-india-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-misb